<HEADLINE>
FT  30 MAR 93 / UK Company News: BAT chief sees pay rise to Pounds 980,679
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir Patrick Sheehy's pay as chairman of BAT Industries rose from Pounds
638,416 to Pounds 980,679 in 1992, the annual accounts showed.
Of this, Pounds 356,250 was performance-related, against Pounds 57,970 last
year. Total directors' emoluments were Pounds 6.4m (Pounds 4.6m), of which
Pounds 2.1m (Pounds 900,000) was performance-related.
The group reported a 68 per cent advance in pre-tax profits to Pounds 1.65bn
in 1992. Earnings more than doubled to 58.7p and the dividend was up 11 per
cent at 37.2p.
