FT  30 MAR 93 / UK Company News: Holmes Protection halts placing
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PAUL TAYLOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
HOLMES Protection, the US security group quoted in the UK, has been forced
to cancel a small share placing after an un-named overseas investor failed
to honour its agreement to pay for 1m shares.
The group, headed by a new management team led by Sir Ian MacGregor,
credited a turnround in its year-end results reported last month to the
successful completion of a three-month debt restructuring programme. The
1.08m share placement was announced at the same time as the year-end
results.
Yesterday the company said sufficient placing commitments had been received,
but that the placing in its present form was being cancelled because of the
problem with the un-named overseas investor.
The group added that it has started legal proceedings against the investor.
The shares were unchanged at 64p yesterday ahead of the announcement.
