FT  30 MAR 93 / UK Company News: Edinburgh Fund Managers up 4.5%
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PHILIP COGGAN, Personal Finance Editor
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
EDINBURGH FUND Managers announced a 4.5 per cent increase in pre-tax profits
from Pounds 4.78m to Pounds 5m in the year to January 31.
Funds under management at the group, which is 54 per cent owned by British
Investment Trust, rose from Pounds 1.91bn to Pounds 2.39bn. Part of that
increase was due to rising stock markets; Pounds 254m of net new money was
attracted during the year.
Since the end of January, EFM has acquired Target Trust Managers, with
Pounds 110m under management. Over the weekend, EFM Dragon, an investment
trust managed by the group, announced that its bid for Drayton Asia, a trust
with Pounds 125m of assets, had gone unconditional.
Private Fund Managers, the private client subsidiary, now has Pounds 235m
under management and made its first significant profit contribution.
Operating profit rose to Pounds 3.87m (Pounds 3.21m). Earnings fell to 18.1p
(18.6p). The final dividend is increased to 8.5p, making a total of 13.5p
(13p).
