CHINA is to buy 12 Airbus aircraft and is considering acquiring a further
nine, Mr Gunther Rexrodt, the German economics minister, ann-ounced in
Beijing at the start of a four-day visit.
A first contract for the purchase of six Airbus A340s is due to be signed
