FT  30 MAR 93 / 'Referendum Movement' breaks from Christian Democrats
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GRAHAM
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Mario Segni, leader of the 'Referendum Movement', yesterday ended months
of speculation about his position inside the Christian Democrat party when
he announced a clean break. His move is likely to have an important impact
on the future composition of the party and its electoral support, writes
Robert Graham. It could prove the first move in a more general political
realignment. Mr Segni, aged 53, is one of the few politicians still with a
strong rating in the opinion polls and has represented a vital clean image
for the party. His decision has been directly prompted by the weekend news
that senior members of the party, including Mr Giulio Andreotti, the former
prime minister, were under investigation for alleged links with the Mafia.
