FT  30 MAR 93 / Parliament and Politics: Health of the Nation conference
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE Department of Health yesterday held a conference to advance the paper
outlining its health strategy, the Health of the Nation.
Mrs Virginia Bottomley, the health secretary, marked the development at a
North West Thames regional conference for the initiative in London. She was
joined by agriculture minister Mr John Gummer.
The conference covered the five key areas of the health initiative; coronary
heart disease and stroke, cancers, mental illness, HIV/Aids and sexual
health, and accidents.
Mr Gummer criticised British eating habits, telling the conference that
although people no longer ate together they should maintain balanced dietary
habits.
